	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are several layers: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>background scenery (clouds, hills, fences, trees) </li><li>foreground scenery (8-3 wall, full-screen water) </li><li>terrain patterns (present/absent rows of blocks) </li><li>area data objects (? block here, pipe here, etc) </li></ol>
<br />One of the area data objects in Y=$C0-$FF changes the foreground scenery; another changes the terrain patterns.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
